https://prez.dev/description.@value: The overarching categorization of vocabularies prepared by the Geological Survey of Western Australia (GSWA).

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: Vocabularies related to the compilation of geological maps, i.e. graphic representations of the distribution, composition and structure of geological materials across the Earth's surface and at depth, depicting both observations and interpretations using symbols and colours. Included here are vocabularies related to topography (the practice of accurately and graphically delineating in detail, as on a map or chart or by a model, selected natural and man-made surface features of a region) and geodesy (the science concerned with the determination of the size and shape of the Earth and the precise location of points on its surface and subsurface), which are fundamental for the correct spatial representation of geological information.
